#3. Participants ##filter values for waves

  filter(WAVE == "t2")

  filter(WAVE == "t3")

cccu_MA_t4 <- cccu_MA%>%
  filter(WAVE == "t4")

  filter(WAVE == "t1")

#Comparision included to excluded sample

t1_comp_inex = rbind(cccu_MA_t1 %>% mutate(exclude = "no"),
                     cccu_excluded_t1 %>% mutate(exclude = "yes"))
table(t1_comp_inex$exclude)
## 
##   no  yes 
## 1723 2911

##hc use

chisq.test(t1_comp_inex$hc, t1_comp_inex$exclude, correct=FALSE)
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test
## 
## data:  t1_comp_inex$hc and t1_comp_inex$exclude
## X-squared = 609.99, df = 2, p-value < 2.2e-16
cramersV(t1_comp_inex$hc,t1_comp_inex$exclude)
## Cramr's V =  0.36
confIntV(t1_comp_inex$hc,t1_comp_inex$exclude, conf.level = 0.95)
## Cramr's V 95% confidence interval (point estimate = .36):  
## Bootstrapped: [.34; .38]  
## Using Fisher's z: [.34; .39]

##contraceptive satisfation

t.test(t1_comp_inex$contra_satis ~ t1_comp_inex$exclude,
       alternative = 'two.sided',
       paired = FALSE,
       conf.level = .95)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  t1_comp_inex$contra_satis by t1_comp_inex$exclude
## t = 1.6113, df = 2936, p-value = 0.1072
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means between group no and group yes is not equal to 0

##  -0.00935594  0.09563539
## sample estimates:
##  mean in group no mean in group yes 
##          3.444573          3.401434

       alternative = 'two.sided',

       conf.level = .95)
